I’ve returned home at last after an arduous journey in the old world. It’s always important to visit other places to remind ourselves of how much better we have it

All jokes about coffee and food aside I really enjoyed my trip to Switzerland, Hungary, and Austria. All 3 are unique within Europe with combos of incredible scenery, architecture, and rich history. 

Switzerland I love for their total independence and high quality of life, if I ever had to live in Europe it’s where I would choose to go. It truly feels different than anywhere else. 

History wise, I especially enjoyed Budapest and Vienna to scratch my interest in the Hapsburgs and Austro-Hungary. At one point, 51 million people were ruled by them and their battles with the Ottomans are legendary. The architecture in both cities is absolutely stunning. 

This trip brings me to having officially visited 22 out of the 44 countries on the continent. Next time I need to get started on the Balkans….

I’ve been piloting this for a few months but put it to the ultimate test in Europe. I brought zero athleisure and didn’t miss it once. I don’t think I’ll go back. Plus it’s fun to dress up for the grocery store or to walk your dog, you just feel different
